Syriatel to Double Capital by Offering Free Share for Each Held

-- B y   L i n a   I b r a h i m
-- 
2011-07-24T12:26:40Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-07-24/syriatel-to-double-capital-by-offering-free-share-for-each-held.html
Syriatel Mobile Telecom SA, one of
two mobile operators in  Syria , received approval to double its
capital by offering one free share for each share held. The
company made the announcement in a mobile-phone text message.  Rami Makhlouf, the cousin of Syrian President Bashar al-
Assad, owns 40 percent in the company.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Lina Ibrahim in Dubai  librahim4@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Riad Hamade at 
 rhamade@bloomberg.net  